** About The Company   
** It is an exciting time to join Eternus. Backed by strong portfolios in financial services and SDA properties, we have been incubating complementary businesses with a view to making more impact. We provide a suite of corporate and professional services designed to extend the capability of our customers and create benefits for people and the community. Our services reflect the needs of dynamic, growing businesses, creating capacity for them to focus on what they do best. These include digital and data, legal, accounting, recruitment, animation and film production, marketing and communication, and travel.   
  
Building from our roots, we incubate and scale our offerings following three
criteria: Virtuous, Profitable, Regenerative. If we are successful, others
will follow. We call this the Eternus Effect.  
  
** About the opportunity **   
The Senior Front-End Engineer position plays a pivotal role in crafting
cutting-edge digital solutions to help sculpt seamless user experiences.
Working with a cross-functional team of engineers and designers, this position
will build a wide variety of rich and engaging React based web applications
and presences.  
  
Some key responsibilities of this role include:  

  * Building rich and highly interactive web experiences, using modern JavaScript frameworks and tooling. 
  * Contributing to agile workshops and planning. 
  * Supporting a collaborative and positive team culture, encouraging knowledge sharing and skill development. 
  * Mentoring other developers, including code reviews and pair programming. 
  * Collaborate with design and product teams to create innovative and user-friendly interfaces. 
  * Develop and maintain front-end codebases using modern JavaScript frameworks and tooling. 
  * Optimise web applications for maximum speed and scalability. 
  * Write clean, maintainable, and efficient code. 
  * Ensure the technical feasibility of UI/UX designs. 
  * Stay up-to-date with emerging technologies and best practices. 
** Criteria   
**

  * Minimum 4 years experience as a Front-End Engineer 
  * Experience in collaborating with designers and understand UX/UI principles. 
  * Advanced JavaScript in major frameworks. 
  * Experience building web apps utilising RESTful APIs & modern front-end tooling. 
  * Experience writing clean, performant and well tested code. 
  * Experience working in remote-first teams, using collaborative tools and processes. 
  * Ability to work across multiple projects for multiple clients. 
  * Excellent problem-solving and communication skills. 
  * Ability to work independently and as part of a team. 
  * Ability to work in an autonomous, remote culture. 
The below capabilities and skills are highly beneficial:

  * Advanced experience with React/Next.js. 
  * Experience with other JavaScript framework 
  * Advanced TypeScript knowledge. 
  * Understanding of WCAG 2.0 accessibility standards and best practices 
** Benefits **   
A competitive remuneration package commensurate with experience will be
offered to the successful candidate.  
**   
** Some current job perks include: **   
**

  * Great flexibility around where you complete your work - and a beautiful, newly refurbished Milton Green office for use. 
  * Extensive Employee Assistance Program (EAP) 
  * Working with an ambitious, energetic and genuine bunch of people in a growing Group, who genuinely want to see you succeed. 
  * A commitment to regularly take time out together to celebrate and develop personal connections with the broader team 
  * Additional paid week of leave 
  * Annual discretionary bonus of up to 20% 
  * An inclusive work environment that prioritises your professional development and growth. 
